cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on human-robot collaboration and the prediction of human motion using skeletal data obtained from RGB depth images. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as well as computer vision (cs.CV) since the skeletal data is obtained from RGB depth images. The paper also uses a conditional variational autoencoder for prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the representation of movements and kinematic cues, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
